@davidfowl

This is to fix `blazor serve`.

The problem was that previously we relied on referencing parts of ASP.NET Core runtime as packages, but since it will ship as shared framework only, we can no longer do that. We now need to use `<FrameworkReference>` to reference ASP.NET Core, but the build system doesn't yet support that for this kind of package.

@natemcmaster is working on adding `<FrameworkReference>` support, so this PR is intended as a *very temporary* workaround to unlock verification that the rest works end-to-end.

